- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with symbolic summation and presents algorithms for finding sum representations. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper mentions the application of the algorithms to evaluate Feynman integrals, which are commonly used in control theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents algorithms for finding optimal nested depth in sum representations. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper may involve logical reasoning in the development of the algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the computational complexity of the algorithms presented.
